{"id":21197,"title":"Loop and uLoop assembly","title_html":"Loop and uLoop assembly","image":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/jhefare.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/jhefare.png"},"doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.yxmfxk6","doi_status":2,"uri":"loop-and-uloop-assembly-yxmfxk6","type_id":1,"published_on":1551995500,"version_id":3,"created_on":1551995415,"categories":null,"creator":{"name":"Bernardo Pollak","affiliation":"J. Craig Venter Institute\/PUC","username":"bernardo-pollak","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/010.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/010.png"},"badges":[{"id":2,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/bronze.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/bronze.svg"},"name":"Author"},{"id":5,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/earlyadopter.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/earlyadopter.svg"},"name":"Early adopter"}],"research_interests":null},"journal":null,"journal_name":null,"journal_link":null,"public":1,"has_versions":1,"link":"","total_collections":0,"number_of_steps":8,"authors":[{"name":"Bernardo Pollak","affiliation":"J. Craig Venter Institute\/PUC","username":"bernardo-pollak","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/010.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/010.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null}],"versions":[],"groups":[],"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"steps":[{"id":718474,"guid":"6398C7C301AE4B82B80961C6E67B6C1F","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7EFCC8BFE9574D708A31FCF898EBE38C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Calculate plasmid target concentrations "}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3142583B3B7544A294FD2B02CE99B274","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The required concentration for each donor part in ng\/\u03bcL\u00a0is plasmid length \/ 100. That will yield a concentration of 15 fmol\/\u00b5L.\u00a0For the receiver plasmid the target concentration is length \/ 200, yielding 7.5 fmol\/\u00b5L.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":718475,"guid":"B246525551D84AE7B79D74C304B67394","previous_id":718474,"previous_guid":"6398C7C301AE4B82B80961C6E67B6C1F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"484B53610B5447CA9C3EEA3D174BBF2F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Prepare DNA mixture"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"83F746D98AC6498BB4A19151DDEC2BA0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add into a PCR tube:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">1 \u00b5L of each donor part at 15 fmol\/\u00b5L.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">1 \u00b5L of receiver plasmid at 7.5 fmol\/\u00b5L.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add water up to 5\u00a0\u00b5L (assemblies from L1 and above do not need adjustment since 5 plasmids are used)<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":718476,"guid":"2216D72B088D49F0AB1F64A5371B31B1","previous_id":718475,"previous_guid":"B246525551D84AE7B79D74C304B67394","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A9F9023AF14B4791A0D7D613E5114DB9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Master mixes"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C029A752DE614232A70437ED143F255E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Odd and even level assemblies use different formulations due to specific requirements of the restriction enzymes used.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">For odd levels (BsaI or BsaI-HFv2), 10x T4 DNA ligase buffer is used.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">For even levels (SapI), 10x Cutsmart buffer is used mixed with 10x T4 DNA ligase buffer in a 1:1 ratio.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">For BSA (bovine serum albumin), check stock concentration. NEB 'molecular biology grade BSA' comes at 20 mg\/mL, depreciated NEB purified BSA comes at 10 mg\/mL. Prepare 20 \u00b5l of 1\u00a0mg\/mL diluted BSA in water solution.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Thaw buffers at RT, then place on ice.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">IMPORTANT:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Do not use BsaI-HF, that enzyme will NOT work with this reaction. Use either BsaI or BsaI-HFv2.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Use aliquoted volumes of T4 Buffer since ATP and DTT will degrade over short amounts of time (less than a month) affecting  the efficiency of the reaction.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">If low efficiency is seen, use double the restriction enzyme volumes.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":718477,"guid":"0FA50103554D468D8100DB2CB24893BA","previous_id":718476,"previous_guid":"2216D72B088D49F0AB1F64A5371B31B1","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"BF4950EA6D8146338F1AD3977C61A64A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Prepare reaction master mix"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"CEFFE47965794B4EBB05E41B09CF371A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">of reactions to be performed and include an extra reaction to account for pipetti5n.g error3s.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">For each odd level reaction:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">\u00a0Odd level BsaI-Ligase 2x master mix:<\/div><table border><tr style = \"text-align:center;\"><td>  <\/td><td>A<\/td><td>B<\/td><td>C<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">1<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colsp